reviews.text: Absolutely fun and family friendly! Could spend all day here! Visited all the way from Tulsa, Oklahoma and was satisfied with the environment! Great place to have a picnic lunch, and to spend time with your family. They have an arcade there as well that is reasonably priced! (Only spent $5 and my daughter played all the games she wanted!) definitely recommend and will be back!

Older hotel, very beautiful place to stay. Walking distance to restaurants, bars and shopping. We had a blast here. The indoor pool was amazing and is also heated. Close drive to the Tennessee aquarium. They also offer a shuttle service. We had an amazing time staying here.

Loved it. Everything was great. Had taken grandchildren and stayed in one of the Pullman cars. All the atmosphere around was liking going back in time. Very neat and well kept place. Swimming pool was very nice also. Great memories with my little ones. We'll be back.
This was a decently fun place. They had games and lots of grass. We played corn hole and there I was also a giant chess set that another family was enjoying. It was fun to see the historic train.

Loved staying in the railcar.  It was special event! Unfortunately the staff is not warm & inviting and there were not enough towels/washcloths places in the room. Loved the gorgeous hotel. I would definitely stay here in future if in Chattanooga area.

Today, we visited the zoo and it was awesome! Yes, it's small but worth it. I loved how close the animals get to the cage and almost want to interact with you. I got awesome pics, and my kids really enjoyed it and they are older. We are huge animal lovers and have visited many zoo but this one is probably the best as far as the encounters go it's not crowded and u can actually see and take wonderful pics without being pushed and worked through crowds. They are adding on, and more animals are too come so I cant wait to visit again in the future! Great work Chattanooga Zoo.

I definitely enjoyed this zoo. I went about 4 years ago, and I have always loved the cute feeling to it. While it’s not one of those big zoos, it has a nice variety of animals like red pandas, snow leopards, Jaguars, chimpanzees, and camels. Not to mention the giraffe coming soon. It had a nice appearance and the people were nice. I especially enjoyed the indoor areas. They had unique indoor creatures too like sloths, iguanas and foxes. The Chattanooga Zoo is a fun experience for the family, but does it beat the Tennessee Aquarium? Most likely.

Great place to spend a few hours. It's certainly not the Knoxville Zoo, but they do have a great selection of animals to keep you interested. I would recommend anyone to check them out. Plus it is very inexpensive. Our family of 5 paid around $55 dollars to get in. Not bad at all. We will go back sometime.

This place is great. It's got daily shows and info surrounding all you'd want to know about the animals. They are currently adding an enclosure to add giraffes, and they have upgraded passes available on site. All of the handlers were super Friendly, and responsive to all of our questions.

I went with my son's preschool field trip. They had a good time but I was a little disappointed. It's nice that they have a pool and playground now but some of the other changes are not so good. No outside food and their food prices are outrageous. $8 for a bag of popcorn and $3 for a bottled water  All they have in the petting zoo are goats.. at least one of which was pregnant and cranky. Actually tried to nip.  A couple of other animals nearby that weren't available to the kids. I was surprised by how few animals they actually had. And I seriously dislike being forced to leave through the gift shop. Are they so hard up for funds? Try explaining to a 5 year old why you can't spend $24 on two stuffed animals.
So much of our history is here! Makes me even more proud to be a Black Woman!!
Very nice place small but nice
Incredible experience. I learned a lot about Louisiana black history.
Great information and pieces!

Our family of 7 went last week and it was so much fun! Our kids range in age from 2-10 and we could have stayed all day (we played for 3+ hours) and still not run out of creative, hands on activities. Educational and fun- we will be back!

We've been to quite a few children's museums all up and down the east coast, this one had plenty of unique things to offer. You're greeted with a pretty impressive climbing area as you walk in. My 6 year old enjoyed this more than our 10 year old. There were water tables to play with underneath. Some of the highlights here were an area dedicated to dinosaurs with an excavation pit kids could dig in, a building area to make robots, a lookout tower, and an area on the roof that demonstrates simple machines. My kids wanted to move on after about 3 or so hours, partly because how many other kids were there and in the case of my 10 year old there wasn't as much for her age to keep her attention. They offer a generous military discount and the staff genuinely seemed to enjoy their jobs.

The best place to take children of all ages. Our older children 10,11 and 12 still love it, and I was so happy to bring our 15 month old a few weeks ago. The little yellow house is perfect for toddlers. He had so much fun.

We was there for a birthday. It was the first time any of is had been at the discovery Museum. It was very fun and entertaining. Lots of fun things for the whole family to do. I hope to visit again. The employees was very helpful.

Lovely place to bring kids - we stopped during a road trip so this was a great kids activity to keep our child entertained, occupied, and learning! I appreciated that there was space to run and play and space for other senses. Bonus that there is a nursing room.

Stumbled across the museum walking around the Bluff View district. I stopped in about 20 minutes before they closed and the staff were friendly enough to offer me an abbreviated version of the regular guided tour. Definitely recommend!

Great surprise!!!  BUT  phone and make sure they are there. Only 2 ladies running it and when I arrived on Wed. At noon they were in a meeting and I had to wait til 12:45. It was worth the wait. Wonderful collection of glass...even some Tiffany pieces. Guided tours are very interesting and played a wonderful anyique music box ... what a treat. They have everything from furnature  toys and snuff boxes!

Great little park, has walking trails around the play area so you can easily exercise while keeping an eye on the kids. Fenced in dog park adjacent to the play area with separate sections for big and small dogs. Note: no kids under 12 allowed in the dog park.
It is amazing for your dog and kids theirs a playground  dog park and room to play soccer or football and walk around for adults
Wonderful dog park.  Good group of regulars that visit.

Beautiful park for families and the dogs! Dog park is pretty clean and is now free, which is nice, but it isn't kept up as well as it should be. I understand it's difficult to have continual upkeep. Still a great park!
Cute park. Great dog park. Watch for mosquitoes and snakes during the summer months though!

I have been wanting to check out Reflection Riding for a couple years, never made time to go, but today I did. This is the most beautiful place around Chattanooga. I definitely did not get to explore every trail or anything, but I will say that my toddler and I had the most magnificent time and will absolutely be back as often as possible!! The trails were clean, and the one employee I talked to was very helpful. There's trails for everyone (skill set wise).

Discovered this place while looking for an alternative to waiting 3 hours for another attraction. So glad we went!!! One of the most gorgeous places I've ever seen! If you have the chance to go here jump on it!!!

First annual Red Wolves 1mile and 5k Race.Great place to visit and walk/run.Thank you Reflection Riding Arboretum and Front Runner and the Red Wolves. Love going to this place many things to see and do. A must visit.
If your looking for a good hike this is a pretty place but the trail are unclear.  So be careful.

What a fantastic landscape at the bottom of Lookout Mountain. Great if you want to spend some relaxing time in a low-intensity landscape where you can roam free. The small patches of garden are great. It's fun to see the array of regional plants that they're growing - I'm excited to see how things continue to develop there. Good for kids, too. As a member, I love being able to visit in the evenings after work - the afterhours program is great.

I have been wanting to check out Reflection Riding for a couple years, never made time to go, but today I did. This is the most beautiful place around Chattanooga. I definitely did not get to explore every trail or anything, but I will say that my toddler and I had the most magnificent time and will absolutely be back as often as possible!! The trails were clean, and the one employee I talked to was very helpful. There's trails for everyone (skill set wise).

Discovered this place while looking for an alternative to waiting 3 hours for another attraction. So glad we went!!! One of the most gorgeous places I've ever seen! If you have the chance to go here jump on it!!!

First annual Red Wolves 1mile and 5k Race.Great place to visit and walk/run.Thank you Reflection Riding Arboretum and Front Runner and the Red Wolves. Love going to this place many things to see and do. A must visit.
If your looking for a good hike this is a pretty place but the trail are unclear.  So be careful.

What a fantastic landscape at the bottom of Lookout Mountain. Great if you want to spend some relaxing time in a low-intensity landscape where you can roam free. The small patches of garden are great. It's fun to see the array of regional plants that they're growing - I'm excited to see how things continue to develop there. Good for kids, too. As a member, I love being able to visit in the evenings after work - the afterhours program is great.

Great place for hand made art, paintings, sculpture, ceramics, jewelry, glass and more.  The people here are great and very accommodating. Worth the stop. Make sure you visit rembrandts coffee and bakery while you're there.
Nice, free gallery. Was greeted at the door, which was nice. 10 rooms of different mediums and styles.
One of the best fine art and craft  stores I know of. Knowledgeable and friendly staff. Outstanding work on display.
Wide variety of art and artistic items,  ranging from high-end to very affordable, with knowledgeable staff.
Great location in the Art District. Great selection of unique art. The staff is friendly, helpful, and knowledgeable.

Took the family to see a production of "Newsies".  What a great time!  The cast was made up of volunteers, most of which were either high school or college students.  It was an excellent performance.  The theater was just the right size and our seats were great, especially for the price!

Very nice small theatre. We saw "A Civil War Christmas", presented in the round; a moving and informative play.
The staff, cast, and crew were all capable and friendly. Highly recommended!

Attended the 2pm performance today. 
Absolutely wonderful.  The Performance was thought provoking,  moving and the voices were spectacular.  Thank you all for a lovely afternoon.

Amazing place.
Great location, very professional.
My daughter is currently taking an acting class there and loves it.
Once on this Island Jr. was Awesome!!;+) Can't wait to go see another show!!;+) I even took my students to see it...They Love It Too!!;+)
The venue is a little dated but it's still a great venue for any act. The Walker Theater especially doesn't have a bad seat period.

Been here many times before and all was well but this time the show started a few minutes late so without notice they closed the concessions before the intermission. And no outside food or drinks was allowed so here we set with the options to do without or drink from the fountain that was install with what one can only assume are the lead pipe from the building original construction (no thanks). Very disappointing. Hope they hire a new coordination leader cause this one is lackluster at best.
Great medium size venue.  Saw Tree Crowder and friends there and really enjoyed the show.
Great place for a concert. Comfortable roomy seating. Awesome sound for vocals.
A great venue. The bathrooms could use some renovating, but overall it is a great place for an event.
My husband's buried here. I will be right next to him as well. I will be honored to be buried here!
Beautiful confederate cemetery. Highly recommend going at night around Halloween!
Beautiful place that is perfectly maintained.  Second in size only to Arlington.  Need to visit especially for Memorial Day or Christmas.
This is the place where I go a visit with the Men and Women who have served our country, feel their presence and know that my Hula Girl is among friends.

Beautiful and inspiring! Personally,  these gorgeous cemeteries always remind me of the debt I owe to all those buried there.  Without them,  our lives would be drastically different.  Their resting place should be beautiful and should promote respect and reverence.  This cemetery captures the very essence of those feelings.  Great place to go pay your respect and beautiful to photograph as well.

This place is fabulous. It's been around for 78 years and I've never heard of it. Great service even greater food. It's a small place that packs a huge punch. You definitely need to put this one on your list of restaurants to try.

Service was fast, waitress was very nice as always. Food very good.
Had Hamburger Steak, baked potato, salad and the famous onion rings.
I have been eating at Nikki's for around 48 years.

One of the must eat at places in Chattanooga and a local legend. Jumbo Gulf Shrimp, Hamburgers and Onion Rings that are bigger than any I've ever seen in my life.  Fairly inexpensive pricing. Friendly and quick service. Usually more of an older clientele but depends on the day.

I'm giving 4 stars because the waitress was very good. Now for the food, I don't know what happened to the burgers. When I saw it it looked like a veggie slider. I was shocked. Bun wasn't even warm. All totalled, we had one veggie burger, a order of onion rings and two cokes. 13 dollars and 75 cents. The tip put it to $18.00. Will not be going back. It's a shame. Y'all used to have the best everything.
Excellent food! Great service! Their shrimp is really good! Make sure you take cash with you or they have an ATM inside.

Cozy Cafe with Soul food and burgers. Friendly atmosphere. Family owned and operated since 1918.
They do not take debit or credit cards. Cash or check only.
Best burger in Chattanooga. And the place has great service, they make you feel like family
I really enjoy going to zarzour's, very good home cooking and I love their cornbread
Awesome place didnt know it was the oldest restaurant in Chattanooga. Also has amazing burgers and fries.
It was very good nice little place to go eat
Nabe is a real sushi chef with experience and a charm about him. This place is the best sushi in town. I love going there every time. Prices are fair. Food is amazing.

Absolutely fantastic sushi with a laid back atmosphere and a real sushi bar. The staff were super friendly and pleasant and could answer any question I had. I wouldn't go anywhere else in Chattanooga for sushi after eating here.

Very small hand rolls, their rice does not taste good. The spicy tuna comes with a sauce that taste like ketchup. The atmosphere is dingy, does not give the vibe of an awesome restaurant although some of the decor is interesting. Service was slow and inattentive, but nice. The fish tasted fresh and was enjoyable. Overall it's okay and is a meal, but we will not be back.

Fantastic eatery.  Closest you will come to authentic Japanese sushi without leaving the country.  The service was great, the quality was pristine, and the presentation was very well done.  I recommend this to anyone who appreciates a well prepared meal.
This place is amazing. Best sushi I have had in a while. Although a little pricey, it's so good for a local restaurant.

I live in Atlanta and make the hour or so drive to Chattanooga for a quick day get away. Big River Grille is sometimes my only destination when I get here. Great atmosphere. Great food. Great service. Great change of pace from the norms of Atlanta.
Food was good.  All of our burgers were cooked proper to order.  The wait staff should remember they are a tourist location also.  She was not very friendly or attentive.  Atmosphere is nice.

Delicious food with A+ service. Expect an up beat atmosphere here. Tons of seating available. Plenty of seats at the bar along with plenty more among the rest of the restaurant. This restaurant sells a surplus amount of brews & drinks with plenty of purchase options. Among those options is a five liter keg good for about 12 glasses of brew. They also offer a wide assortment of fine wines. As a whole the restaurant is smoke free. They also offer billard tables & live music. If your looking for a very fun place to dine in then this location will not disappoint you.

Always great food. The shrimp and lobster quesadillas are fantastic and if you're looking for a great burger get the Bison burger! We enjoy sitting in the outside dining area and watching people and the horses and carriages go by. I must say that our server was less than attentive this time but not enough to ruin the experience.

The bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers were delicious! We also had the big pretzels for an appetizer, which had a salty and garlicky taste. My son loves his flame grilled burger (it was very yummy, I tried it!). Not impressed with the service,  and expected a cleaner facility. Good food but we wouldn't go back.

Actually enjoy everything about this place. Wish it was in more locations nationally. Great service but floor was wet and watched a lady fall. Otherwise perfect. Excellent beer selection and the wings were also above grade. Try them if it's your first time.

I went to this Taco Mac for my birthday. It was the biggest mistake of the weekend. The bartenders were slow. We sat and waited I know at least ten minutes before anyone would acknowledge us. We got our beers. One of the two drinks were incorrect. Whatever, it was beer. Ordered a second round and both drinks were wrong. It took another ten minutes after that to get the check despite.  At this point, I do not ever want to step foot in another Taco Mac. My money will be spent elsewhere and I encourage anyone that actually knows their beer to stay away as well.   And to add, the tables around us weren't bussed the entire time we were there.
I love Taco Mac’s wings. They are absolutely the best wings. Get the slow burn and blue cheese dressing. You can also get all drums for a small charge.
My time here was enjoyable. Our server Jeanette was very attentive and pleasant. And not to mention the drinks were good too.

Amirah was the best server! She was attentive and intuitive. I would definitely request her when I return. I pick my favorites off the menu and I wasn't disappointed. My drinks were mixed well and had a nice pour
Veggie calzone was delicious and gigantic. Went on Tuesday for half off tall boy domestics and they had a great selection. Staff was friendly and attentive.
Great atmosphere with great service. You can't go wrong with this place. We ordered our food and we got it quick! Great selection of beers too!

We came from Georgia where I first encountered this chain. Over there the pizza was amazing. Simply to die for. And when we moved here I was so excited to see that there was a location near us. We drove from Lafayette to dine here because we loved the locations in Georgia so much. I was so disappointed. More like heartbroken. Our buffalo pizza stopped being made halfway up the pizza leaving a thick piece of crust. Our bbq chicken side was burnt. We asked for no onions on both sides there were onions. The crust was not like the other locations. It was hard. My son got the pretzel bites the only good thing that came to our table. It's what I expected my crust on my pizza to be. Our waitress forgot about us once it got busy. The host was the only reason this place got 2 stars. She was amazing and so friendly with my son. I think it needs to meet the management at other locations. Next time we will wait till I visit my in laws in Georgia. Such a huge let down. And dont tell me about it being burnt because it goes into an oven when 2 completely different locations have the same crust and same quality of food on the opposite sides of Georgia. There's something not right with this location.
A very clean  restaurant. Friendly staff not afraid to smile an say hello. Good food. Overall a pleasant experience
Great Pizza! Good servers with efficient service and decent serving time. Try the House special and the mighty meaty! The spinach dip is great too.

Please read edit!!  The best burger around by far!!! Make sure you go crazy with the topping... 
                    !!!!unfortunate edit!!!!!              made our 2 hour trip to cheeburger first time in about 8 months. Complete change of menu. No toppings anymore!!! The once famous and fabulous huge burger with all the toppings is now just a 1/3 lb fast food burger. The super large fry is now a small basket.  While the burger was good, it isn't a burger I would go out of my way to eat. We have made this trip many times a year for 9 years. Can't say as I see us ever going back.

Absolutely delicious. Just be aware that on the new menu, the BLT is not a bacon, lettuce and tomato burger, it is a wrap/sandwich. You can always build your own burger to include bacon, lettuce and tomato. The Onion rings are DELICIOUS!!!!!!! The fries are good too. The restaurant also specializes in unique style milk shakes.
They are offering breakfast now and it's great.  "Make your own omelet"  and hashbrowns/eggs/pancakes plate with fruit are really good!

We aren’t from here and a group of 5 of us came in within an hour of closing on a business trip from out of state. We didn’t realize they were closing soon and they didn’t treat us like it either. We realized how late for them we came in ...shortly after ordering. We ordered big, our food was fresh, timely, accurate, and the service was fantastic. They kindly let us stay a half hour after close while we were mindful of not overstaying our welcome. Our shakes to-go were tasty, very visually appealing and absolutely amazing, big and quality was worth the price. Big tasty burgers, great apps, impressive list of cold beer. The onion rings are to die for. Very sweet service here. Thank you for letting us enjoy our visit!!!!!
96 Health Department score. Clean dining area and restroom. Delicious burger, served hot and relatively quick. Veteran discount given

If I could give no stars I would. The place is dated. They have too many stipulations due to they're in a residential area. The owners ate our food and drink at the reception mean while they police the event as if we're kids. Would not recommend this place to anyone.
This place is Nice

This venue was definitely NOT worth our money or aggravation! Let me start by saying this venue is incredibly beautiful inside and outside, it was perfect for our outdoor fall wedding.  The owner was completely useless to us, we only actually met her one time and had to meet her assistant for any issues. We could get over not meeting with the owner but one month before our wedding we were told we would no longer have use of their linens or china, this was a nightmare and we had no time or money to get a new venue. We ended up buying our own table cloths and some china and using plastic china from Walmart and dollar tree which was heart breaking after having my heart set on china for everyone. On our wedding day we got to the venue and it was FILTHY! our wedding party had to scrub tables and sweep the floor before we could set anything up, not to mention you could stick to the nasty floor and see trash overflowing from outside! I sent the owner a text before we cleaned to see if we could get the cleaning crew to come in but she didn't respond until we had already cleaned up. Someone did finally come in to "clean" but mostly just ran around yelling at our wedding party and families who were cleaning. We even had to blow leaves so we could walk down the isle which we were yelled at for because they claimed they were going to come back and do that later. Our family members took over set up from there so we could go relax and get dressed but it just got worse, Come to find out this cleaning person was still running around yelling and had called the manager claiming we had broken down doors and stolen china and linens, I ended up getting a very rude call from the owner while getting ready and after being accused of breaking down doors and taking things we didn't I was enraged! We even had all the receipts just in case but nothing else was ever said. Despite the drama with the venue our wedding was beautiful and we enjoyed our day despite their attempt to ruin it.

The venue is pretty. However, It looks like it hasn't been used in months. Very dirty and I doubt they would pressure wash for you. They never get back to you on emails or answer the phone. They don't allow outside caterers or vendors. Its all in house for food and alcohol. For heavy horderves its $34 a person. Ridiculous.  There are many other nice venues on bodies of water that allow outside vendors. Keep looking.
Good place for events very pretty setting

Just like the one at home. They have huge screens and are a good size for large parties. They can accommodate a large group. Please call in advance for large parties. Good selection at the bar, all your favorite drinks and some local brew. I went back the next day and was treated just as good. I liked the service and the staff was really trying to get me everything I asked for.

The food is set by the company, and the back end fulfills their end of the deal by making great, casual food. However, the front end customer service leaves something to be desired. Too long to come back to table. Little menu knowledge (this has been on three occasions in the past month). If you want to watch the game and dont care about customer service, then 5 stars.
The patron was very attentive and very helpful. The appetizers were delicious and the pulled pork sandwich could have used less salt but overall good. There were no images due to the gobbled up food.
The food was good but what made the experience even better was our server!! She was amazing... just wished I could remember her name.  I would hire her in a heartbeat

Atmosphere is their main attraction. The wings are ok. Let's face it you go for the drinks and sports.  However the burger never disappoints.  Bloody Mary could use some tweaking.  I've had better. Can't mess up the draft drinks. Service is slow so order a drink before you get to the glass half-empty.

Great Food! Great Service!  We got there at 6:15 pm on a Friday.  We thought they were open until 8:00 pm based on the website but no. They took us in and fed us good.  The people were extra friendly. We love this place.

The food itself is good.  Can't complain about that, but the service and demeanor of the people who work there will ensure that I never step foot in this establishment again.  I had obtained a living social offer, and was greeting with aggression obtaining it.  We had two of the deals that are prepaid for, and were going to use them both.  The owner was telling us that we could not use them both, in which case we said we would pay the difference.  He continued on telling us that for six orders would be one table, when in reality there are no tables in the building, that I saw, that could seat 6 people.  When we informed him that we would sit 3 to a table he got even more infuriated.  He then proceeded to tell us that he had to make money too.  Why put an offer or coupon available to the public if you don't want it used. We asked what the difference was for the one we were going to use to which he replied don't worry about it and he walked off.  We left both vouchers at the register and left, without our drinks, but it was already uncomfortable and shouldn't have happened.  So I say, food is good, service and temperament not worth dealing it with so many other options.
Consistently good.  Everytime I come here it is the exact same and exactly as good as the time before.  I have never had a bad experience here.  Try the Brisket Plate.

This is a winner. Bar-B-Que is real Bar-B-Que. Plates are moderately priced. The fries and cold slaw is good but I love the shredded beef brisket!. No sauce needed. The flavor can stand on its own. My wife loves the pulled pork. The waitress provided us with efficient friendly service. The place was clean and has great atmosphere. I understand President George Bush ate there a few years ago, but I try not to hold that against the owner. ; -) I do wish  they had better parking. I learned that there is free meter parking on the street after 4:30 PM. which helps some. I also like ordering carry out by the pound for eating later.
End of an era. Loved this place, but today is the last day. They are starting a food truck and keeping the catering business.

One of the better options for Japanese food in Chattanooga. The building is nice and never feels crowded, probably because it has such nice high ceilings. Classic old brick exterior wall, nicely finished. Extensive menu, including early bird options and a sushi buffet on Friday’s at lunch time. Great value and very pleasant service.

Had vegan options and I have to say - Best vegan sushi I’ve ever had! Creative and delicious, I was pleasantly surprised. I had the Buttercup Roll. Staff was very friendly and food came quickly. Will definitely be back next time we’re in Chattanooga :)

There isn't many things I can eat anymore. 
I ordered the vegetable rolls.  Loved them! The lady that took my order, I believe was one of the owners, was so kind.  I would definately recommend this place.

Not sure what happened. I've heard only good things about Sekisui. My first experience here, ordered two chicken teriyaki delivered for dinner. Both were overcooked and tasted overly charred. Portions were surprisingly small for the price. Not impressed. Would not recommend.

Last night, my girlfriend and I wanted some good sushi in Chattanooga and we looked online. I never do ratings but I feel like I should this time. We saw that the health rating was 79 but we figured it wasn’t the food it was maybe the cleanliness either way we should’ve listened. I ordered 2 rolls the crunchy crab and spicy tuna which has the raw tuna in it. I’m not sure what it was, maybe the crab meat or the raw tuna. All I do know is I woke up today with a really bad stomach burning sensation(not a good one) and diarrhea.

I don't live in Chattanooga, but every time I drive through Chattanooga I make sure it's during the happy hour at Beast + Barrel. I don't think I've ever been to a better happy hour anywhere. They have fantastic food options for cheap and a great TN draft list too! I suggest just ordering the entire happy hour food menu. Also, the back porch is dog friendly so you can bring your pup's. Every server I've ever had there was wonderful. I'm telling you, go here for happy hour - you will thank me later.
Beast and barrel had a pretty neat interior. The service was top notch. During brunch you'll have access to a bloody Mary bar. I've always had great food there too.
First time eating here and we are not locals. I thought the food was amazing. My husband said it was a little on the hipster side. Overall great experience!

There for Saturday lunch between brunch and lunch menus. Service was horrible as well as the martinis and champagne by the glass. Fries were lukewarm. Pastrami sandwich was good. Sat in the bar section which one would hope to have better service. This is the 3rd time to visit here. Overall, food is fair, service slow and neither is predictable.

This place NEVER let's me down. Whether you're looking for a quick brunch, snack, drink, or a nice dinner this place offers it. While their menu is small, I thoroughly enjoy it. The few things they do offer, they excel in. 

The ribeye with the goat cheese whipped potatoes and the seasonal risotto has my mouth watering as soon as I walk in the door. They certainly know how to cook a steak there. The staff is always coming by to check on you and making sure your drinks are always full, but they don't overburden you either. It's a very remarkable line they walk. 

The bar keepers knows many different types and styles of drinks, and are quiet exceptional at making them. They have a huge cocktail list, and the prices are reasonable too. 

Why you would pay the same price at Longhorns or Outback is beyond me. If you haven't visited this place yet. I sure hope this review helps.

Great little place with BBQ and sandwiches.  There is some customer parking in front of the building making this a easy right-turn in and out if you are taking Ochs Highway up the Mountain.  I like that two types of slaw are offered on the BBQ sandwich; I choose spicy... delicious!  It was within 30 minutes of closing time when I got there.  The friendly wait staff were attentive even as they performed end of day duties.

This is by far the best BBQ ribs and chicken I have ever had.  I came a long way to eat hear and was not disappointed.  If you are in the area be sure to stop by.  The restaurant does not look like much but believe me, once you eat hear you will be back for seconds.  The only reason I can't do that is that I live hundreds of miles from here.  Overall, really delicious food!!

This was so yummy!!! Such an awesome meal! We stopped here for lunch before visiting the incline. Very retro looking ! I ordered barbecue stuffed baked potato it was the yummiest meal ever! My only critique was the seating was very uncomfortable and there was not very much seating!

We were passing through on an unplanned trip and found this place. The waitress, Kesha B, recommended the stuffed potato. It was cooked perfectly and the taste was yummy! I chose the pork.  My hubby chose the two item combo. He was happy as well. The only sad part is, we were too stuffed to try the banana pudding pudding. We recommend trying this place!

It's classified as BBQ, but I wouldn't really call it that. The food they had was good and the service was fast. the waitress did take a little bit to get the check when a baby shower came in but other than that everything was good.

I love the Chop House. The food is hands down the best in Ann Arbor. We always go for the cheese platter appetizer and it is some of the best you will find. The prices are a little steep but once you taste the food, it is well worth it. The cocktails are alright and they need a bit more mixing before being served as they aren't a uniform flavor but outside of that, I highly recommend this place for an anniversary or birthday or just a nice date. Their cigar lounge is high quality and the atmosphere is perfect. I will always come back to this place.

A couple weeks ago, we enjoyed a dinner elsewhere in Ann Arbor and decided to head to Chop House after for an espresso and cigar. After a half mile walk we arrive to find out the cigar bar is non smoking due to a private party. Fine. No problem, we should have called. Tonight, we did the same thing. Except we called first to make sure the cigar lounge was open, we called, yes it’s open. Perfect, we walk there. Guess what, closed. Continuous bad service from this place. It’s overpriced we all know that, but it used to at least have good service. Not anymore. Save yourself the dull experience and go to the steak house around the corner.

The steaks were tender and thick and all of the appetizers were great. We also had very good service. It's a pretty fancy establishment. And they offer great discounts for birthdays. Roughly enough to make the birthday persons meal free, given that it's on the actual birthday.

Went here on two occasions. One was my girlfriend's birthday. It was a wonderful time. The staff were friendly and very speedy, and food was amazing. However, when I went for my club's business conference, it was a bit hectic-- understandably. Several orders were messed up, but they were corrected surprisingly fast. Overall, a great place to dine!

Pretty awesome place. Went doing restaurant week where you get a 3 course meal or something for $28. I ended up taking my wife for her birthday and got their birthday discount. Got the 11oz steak, calamari, mashed potatoes, and asparagus. All was good. Bathroom was nice and clean but a little intimate since everything is in one little corner. Ambience was great. Recommend seeing Kiara for best service. Overall great experience.

What a fun place to go with a family that is really hungry and ready for some entertainment. This dining experience was entertaining from the start. Immediately as you get to the restaurant outside you have beautiful Japanese garden with some gorgeous prize-winning goldfishes. They kids had so much fun looking at them swimming and everything.  After all of that excitement we were able to be seated at a Japanese Hibachi Table with another family and kids so my children had a lot of fun interacting with everyone else around the table. As the chef came in he quickly started his show and it was fun interactive and very energetic. There was so much food!!!! Your portions are very large so make sure you come hungry. the typical Hibachi chicken dinner included rice vegetables and before that you get to have soup and salad. The only reason I took a star of was that the food was not as flavorful or authentic as I am used to but for being Japanese attraction chain spot it was sort of expected to be a little Bland however it was perfect for kiddos taste buds.

The food is surprisingly better than one might think. The salad that comes out with the soup prior to the meal is delicious I really like the dressing here. I did not care for the sushi as it did not seem as fresh as some places. The steak and chicken combo I ordered was well-cooked and affordable.

We arrived around 5:30, no one else in the dining area except for a group that was finishing up. We waited 15-20min before getting our drinks. A party of 16 arrived after we got our drinks. We had already ordered when another group joined our table. We still had not received our salads or soup an HOUR after being seated, but the party’s food was being cooked and served. Poor management. We were told that the party arrived before us, when they actually MOVED us from the table the party was sitting at to serve us quicker. The manager that I spoke with said “they knew what they wanted to eat, they had a list” I DON’T CARE if they had a list, we had ordered our food BEFORE the party placed their order. Waiting an hour and not receiving soups and salads is unacceptable in my book.

This place has always been pretty good. However the service has really gone down hill. No refills for the entire meal. Wrong food served. Appetizers brought after meal. Very small portions. Time to search for new place to eat.

Yes yes!! Best sushi presentation in Tennessee. Chef Boy knows how to make a birthday special. I told him to surprise me and yes I was surprised with a great sushi dinner.. will always be my go to place for sushi!!

Are you kidding me? I called ahead for 12 people 5 of them being small kids. I had to wait another 45 minutes after the call ahead time to get seated and I repeat with 5 small children. Are you kidding me? Is the call ahead not done for that particular reason that I don’t have to spend an hour waiting for a table with small children? I don’t understand. The host not only is standing there giving me an issue but also making comments about how he can’t do anything. Perhaps you shouldn’t be making a call and head if you cannot accommodate. Disgusting! Very disappointed my last time here.

Excellent service that evening and the steaks were cooked to perfection. I strongly recommend people tell them to leave their seasoning off because it really ruins s a good piece of meat.  I loved that the sweet potato was not in foil so it was actually a sweet potato and not pudding.  The New York strip was amazingly tasty for the price. Our waiter was really on top of things and kept our glasses full and kept checking to see if we were satisfied. The salads were very fresh and tasty. I do recommend the wedge salad because it is excellent and a good value.

Wow Wow Wow. Had a great meal. Service was outstanding.  The waiter Michael was a step above all before.  We both had a special.  Lobster tail and Sirloin - and - Lobster tail and Crab Cakes and Shrimp skewer. A couple beers and the Awesome brownie.  Looking forward to going back and asking for the same waiter Michael!

I tried something new this visit and had the Pork Porterhouse. It was cooked perfectly, properly cooked and still juicy. It was very savory and I was very happy with my selection. The waiter, though he got our order correct and sufficiently attentive, while he was standing in front of our table seemed like we were keeping him from something more important. It was a typical Outback, so nothing to write home about with the decor. We were seating at the first booth from the lobby, so we saw quite a bit of foot traffic. In general, a nice meal with the delicious piece of pork being the best thing of the night.

Terrible experience yesterday. 3:45 in the afternoon and half the restaurant is empty! We were told to wait for 40 minutes until a waiter came on duty to wait on us🙄😡
So we left and went to Texas Roadhouse where we received amazing treatment with excellent customer service. 
We will not go back to Outback ever!!

The food was really good. Our waitress was having a bad day though couldn't seem to get anything right. I have to say this is unusual for Red Lobster. Hopefully she will get better as the day goes on.

Not what it was before.  Prices went up and you get less food.  The service was some of the worst I've ever had.  We waited about 10 minutes for our waitress.  Then again for her to take our order.  Then after about 15 minutes we got our meal.  No salads or the soup my wife ordered.  Then asked for more bread we never got it.  We had this wait person last time and she messed up our order.  So sad to see how far Red Lobster has fallen.

Food is way over priced. Good food. Not great. I don't know that I will ever go back, except for takeout. Service was also good. 100 dollars for 2 people to eat is just crazy for the quality of food we had.

It has been years since I have been to Red Lobster. I enjoyed it so much before. But this visit could have been a lot better. At first it was just a dirty fork. From there it went to a changed recipe of the coconut shrimp and lobster. Now it's a Cajun recipe which is not mentioned on the menu. So my wife's mouth is on fire. They exchanged it for shrimp scampi but forgot to bring her side she originally ordered. Everything else was good, but this is my reason for only two stars. And it makes me feel hesitant for a return visit.
Love lobsterfest. Karen my waitress was amazing. She made me a happy birthday ice cream desert. Wonderful birthday dinner. I loved the crab legs

Wow! Family oriented but also has a bar for singles if they want to be alone. Good food, drinks, and service. Only thing I don't like is those electronic monitors( or whatever they're called) on every table. Will be back again and would suggest other folks check it out. Yummy garlic bread sticks that go so well with everything!

Had a fantastic dinner here with my wife. Service was prompt and professional. Rarely had to wait. Everything was just perfect and I figured it deserved a good review. Thank you guys for the great service. I'll definitely be back again

We went for dinner service during All You Can Eat Stuffed Pastas. After being seated, we sat for about 5 minutes without seeing our server, but once she showed up, the food started rolling in, and boy, did it keep coming. We ordered libations from the bar, and they appeared in no more than 2 minutes. Plates were always fresh and tasty.  Presentation could have used a little love, but all was forgivable given the number of patrons and speed of service.

Olive garden rarely disappoints! Today was lovely. I can't rememeber the servers name but she was on fire today. Polite, helpful, patience. Drinks were always full, the communication was something that I was so happy to see. 
Only thing I can really critique is, my beloved olive garden salad. What have become of thee? I wish the salad had a little more love in it! The lettuce was barely chopped. 3 olives, 2 slices of tomato, and not nearly enough dressing.
Look, olive garden. I know you've made your dressing available in stores for awhile now. But there still isn't anything like bottomless soup and salad. 
Please hear my plea! Bring back the delectable, tasty, satisfying, salad the way it used to be!
Yummy as always!  Had 2 apps and dinner - seafood alfredo - all was delicious.  Fast, friendly, attentive service. Clean restaurant and restrooms!  Great dinner!

Some of the best food and sushi around. The cooks are insanely friendly and cook the food perfectly. You definitely get your monies worth especially for kids meals. They have a wide selection of alcohol to drink as well. Their sauces are next level. You can also find coupons for Hana pretty easily to save an easy $5 or more. It's really nice to go and watch some sports or go for a date night. You can also get the food to go and it's just as good. Definitely a very family friendly environment and a nice and relaxing time.

The Chef was great, he really put on a show. The food was good. We came in for my daughter's birthday, a party of sixteen. She loves hibachi and wanted to try Hana. Someone made the decision to give a party of 16 to a server only on his second day at work. Horrible decision.  Very slow, salads didn't come out until the food was done, only half of the party got them in the first place. Soup was even later. Most of, if not everyone sat with empty glasses the entire time.   Just was not the best experience at all. When management was approached. Not to get anyone in trouble, but to let them know they were full of it they weren't very apologetic. To top it all off the server put gratuity on everyone's check. For a second day at work, he knew he sucked and still decides to charge us an extra 18 percent. He didn't deserve it. My family will never dine at Hana again.
Best hibachi, best dressing and sauces. Wonderful cooks. Been going  there since I was 10. Changed names and a few things on the menu.Better than ichiban ,shogun, or Fuji hands down.

Our chef was very good and interacted wonderfully with my 6 year old for his birthday lunch.  He shaped a minion out of the fried rice for him, and but a candle in his "birthday cake" of fried rice.  He then led the table in singing Happy Birthday.  My son was thrilled.

We were disappointed in Hana.  We ordered the calamari to start. It consisted of a handful of fried out-of-the-bag calamari tossed on a plate with some type of white garlic sauce.  Not well seasoned nor very hot and over cooked.  
The sushi rolls we just ok. The volcano roll was over cooked and the spider roll had no flavor.  We're new to the area and were told Hana was decent, but we will be looking elsewhere next time.

Good food.  Reasonably priced. The shrimp special was delicious.  But the wife's steak came out under-cooked.

A few mistakes were made with the service, hence the lower rating.  But this is a better choice if you're in the neighborhood.

We love Logan's decided to stop while coming home from vacation,  grilled mushrooms was still cold and uncooked. I did end up returning my pile high french dip, it was the outer part of the roast one half of the sandwich 1/3 of the meat was uneatable the other half was uneatable they removed it from the bill and made me a new one but it should of never made it out of the kitchen.

I am a truck driver and our terminal is practically next door. As a reward to myself I come here EVERYTIME  I am in town. Probably not again. 
It took 10 minutes for the waitress to even acknowledge my existence, ordered my usual meal and a side salad. Over a half hour goes by and out comes my steak..... no salad... no big deal just asked them to forget the salad(appetizer) when I cut into the steak which was ordered medium it was medium well, almost well done.
So long story short, I know as a server you hate single diners but we eat too and a little secret we usually tip quite well. ( at least I do)
So pay attention to the big parties and keep ignoring your loyal customers.
Now I guess it's off to find food.
Great food. Our waitress was great but she had no one else helping her so she was everywhere. Still did a decent job.

This place is such a joke. Never have I seen such a poorly managed place. This is the second time it has happened where they have like twelve empty tables but they refuse to sit people because their kitchen is backed up or whatever. I mean seriously? Let's have people stand up and not even get drinks because our back of the house is poorly run? If they weren't the only place in Lookout Valley they'd be closed. The managers need to go work in another industry because they don't understand service.

Then it gets worse. We're finally seated, and we're seated as far away from TV's as possible. We ask can't we just sit at one of those other 12-15 empty tables closer to a TV. The hostess says she will check, then she comes back and says no. What is going on with this place?

In the end I decided they weren't worth my money and we just ordered drinks until the game was finished and went and ate somewhere else. That is how bad the customer service was here, I decided I would rather drive somewhere else to eat just to deprive them of revenue I felt they didn't deserve.

Tried to order online and it wouldn't process so when I called 15 minutes later they said it was too late to place a phone order, I would have to come in to the restaurant.  I received good service at the restaurant but the steak was tough and had a lot to gristle in it. My ribs however were good as were the garlic mashed potatoes.

Applebees is always a good choice with all the options available. What I love most is they have delicious low calorie options without sacrificing the quality or flavor. There are usually great drink specials as well. Don't forget the happy hour options either!

Normally don’t have problems with Applebee’s but this particular location did not impress or even fulfill its purpose. Stopped in after a day of travel and we were seated quickly and our food came out quickly but the boneless wings were completely uncooked on the inside. Manager finally came over and said he would take care of the meals but never came back to confirm it was taken care of or told the waitress it was taken care of. Employees were loud and yelling about shifts and schedules and using a table near ours as a break room table. It was very unprofessional and a disappointing evening.

We went before the dinner on hour, it was basically empty except for the bar area. We had all you could ear of chicken tenders, ribs, Fry's, and slaw and my daughter had the chicken alfredo. Service was very good and very attentive to our needs. Very good place to eat. Just off the interstate so easy access.
Food was ok, under seasoned. Had broccoli cheese soup (yummy) and bourbon chicken shrimp (less than yummy). Great service and fun atmosphere, though. I'll be back!

What a fun place to go with a family that is really hungry and ready for some entertainment. This dining experience was entertaining from the start. Immediately as you get to the restaurant outside you have beautiful Japanese garden with some gorgeous prize-winning goldfishes. They kids had so much fun looking at them swimming and everything.  After all of that excitement we were able to be seated at a Japanese Hibachi Table with another family and kids so my children had a lot of fun interacting with everyone else around the table. As the chef came in he quickly started his show and it was fun interactive and very energetic. There was so much food!!!! Your portions are very large so make sure you come hungry. the typical Hibachi chicken dinner included rice vegetables and before that you get to have soup and salad. The only reason I took a star of was that the food was not as flavorful or authentic as I am used to but for being Japanese attraction chain spot it was sort of expected to be a little Bland however it was perfect for kiddos taste buds.

The food is surprisingly better than one might think. The salad that comes out with the soup prior to the meal is delicious I really like the dressing here. I did not care for the sushi as it did not seem as fresh as some places. The steak and chicken combo I ordered was well-cooked and affordable.

We arrived around 5:30, no one else in the dining area except for a group that was finishing up. We waited 15-20min before getting our drinks. A party of 16 arrived after we got our drinks. We had already ordered when another group joined our table. We still had not received our salads or soup an HOUR after being seated, but the party’s food was being cooked and served. Poor management. We were told that the party arrived before us, when they actually MOVED us from the table the party was sitting at to serve us quicker. The manager that I spoke with said “they knew what they wanted to eat, they had a list” I DON’T CARE if they had a list, we had ordered our food BEFORE the party placed their order. Waiting an hour and not receiving soups and salads is unacceptable in my book.

This place has always been pretty good. However the service has really gone down hill. No refills for the entire meal. Wrong food served. Appetizers brought after meal. Very small portions. Time to search for new place to eat.

Yes yes!! Best sushi presentation in Tennessee. Chef Boy knows how to make a birthday special. I told him to surprise me and yes I was surprised with a great sushi dinner.. will always be my go to place for sushi!!

I wish I could leave 6 stars out of 5. Absolutely outstanding experience, food, & prices. I don't have high enough regard for the taste of the food. Anything you order here will have you moaning in delight. The staff is so attentive, the music is very peaceful, & they took a lot of time to create a fine dining experience. As if there wasn't enough good things to say, the prices are very within budget! My dinner entree was about $10-11. The portions are plenty. Lastly, I want to say everytime I've been to Sweet Basil, it's been this same amazing experience.

We ate here for dinner. The food was excellent  and the waitress was friendly and spot on. She made sure we always had a full glass and made sure our food was good. The sushi was the best I have ever had. We couldn't have had a better experience.

I was looking for somewhere to eat while I was working in Chattanooga and based on Google maps and reviews decided to give them a try. The service was fantastic! I was seated right away by the hist. My server followed closely behind. The food was very good. The portion size was perfect, just full enough. I would most certainly eat here again.

Great value, really nice people and great service. We think it’s the best Thai place in town. We’ve been going here for years but only recently tried the Bento box. Japanese idea, but they did it with Thai flair and it works!
This is my first time eating here and I really enjoyed the atmosphere! Sweet Basil Thai is a hidden gem! Come and enjoy a peaceful place with sweet people.

Golly whoppers serves up a pretty decent deli sandwich. At first it can seem a little over priced but the portions are huge. a half sandwich combo is more than enough to fill you up. On a busy day the line.can get quite long so plan accordingly. There is plenty of parking in the shopping plaza so that's rarely a problem. The restaurant is decorated in bible and Christian themed decor which is fine but it is a bit overwhelming.

Food is good, service so-so. 

Went to buy the half-sandwich, drink, and chip chicken salad combo for 7.99. Staff looked at me like I had 2 heads for saying I would like my chicken on a small bed of lettuce instead of bread b/c I wanted to go low-carb. Cashier then proceeded to turn my 7.99 order into 11.99 b/c he claimed I wanted a salad--an oh so overpriced salad- and then proceeded to charge me for a drink and chips. 

If I ever go back again, I will be compelled to list in minutest detail exactly what I'm looking for. 

-Kara
Great food.

Hostess took her time sitting us. Left people waiting over 20 min. One lady left because she only had one hour for lunch. If she had moved any slower they would of buried her. Our waiter was the best. He checked with us often and made sure all his tables were happy!

Not a great brunch place, but those skinny potatoes kicked butt.  Nice servers.  The veggie omelette had huge chunks of broccoli in it. I wouldn't have ordered it if the menu mentioned broccoli. Luckily my wife swapped plates with me.  Stick to the menu please, don't substitute and not ask me.  And my goodness, chop up the broccoli a bit.

My overall experience last night was awful, and I can say with all honesty that I won't be visiting here again. 

The restaurant was not busy, however, it took a long time to seat myself and my daughter. The server took an incredibly long time just to take our drink orders, and another 15 minutes to take the food orders. I'll be honest, I wasn't born with a highly superior autobiographical memory, and neither was our server, but she attempted to take our order without writing it down. I ordered the steak and salmon well done and a cheese pizza for my daughter. The food comes out, and
and there are chicken strips and steak. The server takes the chicken strips off of my plate (I hope they don't recycle the food) and goes to the back. I then cut into my steak and it is medium well. They discounted the meal, but I was so displeased. It was all wrong. I won't be returning here, ever.

Flavor was spot on but temperatures were way off. Cold, hard undercooked potato,  Luke warm broccoli and a tepped fatty steak. Could have been excellent,  but from the lack luster greeting at the door it should have been a sign that things are not managed well. I sat facing the "to go" counter and felt deeply sorry for the folks thinking they were going to grab and go. There was an average wait time of 25 minutes.  Saw people dress like managers but we were never approached or greeted by one.
Nice and clean. The only reason they get a four star is because they did not greet me when I entered. If this food was for me I would not have bought it, I would have took my money elsewhere.

The website was amazing with great reviews, so I was excited to go.  We are world travelers and foodies. When we get there, items on the website we’re not available, nor on the menu at all!!  What was on the menu was lack luster and disappointing.  I love tapas and the small bites of deliciousness...this place did not deliver.  Lobster bisque was fishy tomato liquid no lobster anywhere.  Cheese platter was disappointing and the blue puff was heavy and dense not light as it should be. Wine was great though!! They need to represent their actual menu on their website so you know what to expect. I would not recommend eating here.

This is our favorite restaurant in town! Grace our waitress has to be the best waitress out there. Food is exceptional!
The smoked salmon is my favorite starter and the beef tips was so tender and tasty. My husband and I gorge ourselves whenever we are here.
What a journey! I've never had so much fun trying different small dishes.  The owner and staff are very personable.  Highly recommend.
Been here many times, the food is always excellent. Worth every penny spent every time. Great place to go when you can't decide on one thing to eat. Invite your friends and it's even better!
Incredible food and incredible service in a welcoming and fun atmosphere! If I could give this more stars I would.

Very nice experience of friendly people and wonderful new tastes. We had the fresh raw oysters and wood grilled squid appetizer. Shared both and took a to-go order of Salmon home we can't wait to try. The squid was delicious! Would definitely go back on our next business trip.

We arrived before happy hour ended. Because our waitress was so busy she could not get to us until after 6.  Anytime we have been seated before Happy Hour ended at other establishments the happy hour special has always been honored. The manager on duty the night of 4/10 would not honor this. Therefore we did not give them our business of dinner which we had been seated after 1 hour wait. Very disappointed. The lady that waited on us at bar very near car and attentive.

Hands down, one of the best seafood restaurants I've been to.   Awesome oysters,  salmon is great.  Great brisket too!  I can't say enough good stuff about this place.   A must visit, which I do, every time I'm in Chattanooga.

Great service Everytime I'm here and Paula is the bomb! Try the hot wings app or the bloody Mary's. They will make your day! The crab roll is excellent when it is available. Overall, such a fun a place to visit and eat with a group!

The oysters are fresh and delicious. Smoked salmon was also excellent. I have been a few times now and everything was tasty and the service has always been top notch. I enjoy sitting on the patio and watching the river.
We were there for a wedding.  And it was a great venue for that.  Good food and service were what I would expect.  Would return sometime to check it out more throughly.

Thanks Giving dinner was a nice spread but a bit odd. Sushi? No ham. White meat only turkey was dry. Way to much mushroom in to many dishes. Nice environment and service was good as buffets go. A little pricey at $35. We were looking to make a new holiday tradition for my wife and me. This didn't make the grade for next year. Sorry.
We got married here in '98 in the "Art Room" was perfect and cozy for our small party of 12. Staff was great.
